  "text": "As any other mm-wave CMOS circuits, both lumpedelement and distributed structures can be employed for mm-wave VCOs. Generally speaking, a purely lumpedelement implementation results in a more compact design, whereas a distributed approach leads to better matching between simulation and measurement results [CITATION_1] .",
